Mpumalanga cops have arrested a suspected drug deal. The 42-year-old man who is out on bail was rearrested on Friday, 25 February 2022 for unlawful possession and dealing. According to police spokesperson Captain Dineo Lucy Sekgotodi they received a tip-off about a drug dealer who was peddling drugs at Jabulani Street next to the mall in Bethal. “On arrival, the team found a male in possession of pieces of rock cocaine and dagga. He was arrested and detained at Bethal SAPS. The suspect was on bail after he was previously arrested for a similar charge on Major Investigation Dream-On as per Bethal case,” she said. According to Sekgotodi during the previous bail hearing, the investigation officer opposed bail, but the court granted him. The suspect will appear in the Bethal Magistrates’ Court on Monday, 28 February 2022.